All the n rounds were conducted one after the other without any break in between. During the competition, for any person, the person who shot at the target immediately before that person (not necessarily from the same round) is referred to as the preceding shooter of that person.

After the n rounds, they noticed that their hits and misses in each round, except the first round, all followed certain rules, which are given below.

For any person, say X, in any round,

  1. if X hit the target in the previous round and his preceding shooter also hit the target, X missed the target in that round.

  2. if X missed the target in the previous round but his preceding shooter hit the target, X hit the target in that round.

  3. if X hit the target in the previous round but his preceding shooter missed the target, X hit the target in that round.

  4. if X missed the target in the previous round and his preceding shooter also missed the target, X missed the target in that round.

Further, it is known that at least one person hit the target in the competition.

The tax that a citizen has to pay under each of the four schemes depends on his/her annual income.

The four schemes are described below:

  1. Scheme A: Flat 12.5% tax on entire income irrespective of the income level.

  2. Scheme B: 5% on entire income for people earning up to USD 100,000; 7.5% tax on entire income for people earning more than USD 100,000 and up to USD 1,000,000 and 20% tax on entire income for people earning more than USD 1,000,000.

  3. Scheme C: 5% tax on entire income for people earning up to USD 500,000 and 20% tax on entire income for people earning more than USD 500,000.

  4. Scheme D: No tax for people earning up to USD 200,000; 10% tax on entire income for people earning more than USD 200,000 and up to USD 1,000,000 and 15% tax on entire income for people earning more than USD 1,000,000.

The government asked the citizens to vote for any one of the four schemes. All the citizens of the country voted exactly once and each citizen chose the scheme which will minimize the tax that he/she has to pay.
